Previously our Japanese customers can use double byte chars in Confluence User Macros.

But as of Confluence 3.4.x this was restricted to only a-z A-Z 0-9 _ and -, see CONFDEV-372 (restricted to Atlassian) and change set 123683. Saving a new user macros using Japanese characters will produce an error:
{noformat}
    User macro names can only contain the following characters: a-z, 0-9 and - 
{noformat}

Also, after upgrading to 3.4.x they had a nasty surprise that the admin console failed to display the characters correctly albeit they still can be used without any problem in their content.

Making this as a bug as previously this was working for our Japanese customers - and we never stated this clearly that we only support English Characters or numbers in our doc: http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Writing+User+Macros

According to this doc: http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Configuring+the+Site+Support+Address the site support address can be modified.

But because the {{value}} field was hard coded to {{$action.getText('mailto.confluence.auto.support.requests')}} in {{editgeneralconfig.vm}} the address cannot be changed:
{code}
#bodytag( "TextField" "label='site.supportaddress'" "name='$action.getText('mailto.confluence.auto.support.requests')'" "theme='aui'" "value='$action.getText('mailto.confluence.auto.support.requests')'" "disabled=!$siteSupportEmailAllowed")
{code}

It should be set to {{siteSupportAddress}} instead without single quotes.

