There is a lot of logic in the various actions in {{com.atlassian.confluence.setup.actions}} which is duplicated in a {{com.atlassian.startup.StartupExtension}} in Studio in order to bootstrap Confluence when a new instance of Studio is provisioned.

Refactor this logic into a service that can be accessed and called in the {{StartupExtension}}. This will reduce the effort needed to maintain the copied code.
